                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-center text-green-700">2. Get Moving</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Aim for at least 150 minutes of moderate exercise per week. A brisk walk, a bike ride, or a dance class are all great options. Find activities you enjoy! This helps your body use insulin more effectively and can help with weight management.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 3: Weight Management -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-300">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/60x60/a8e063/ffffff?text=âš–ï¸" alt="Scales Icon" class="card-icon mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-center text-green-700">3. Manage Your Weight</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Losing even a small amount of weight (5-7% of your body weight) can make a huge difference in preventing type 2 diabetes. Focus on sustainable habits rather than quick fixes. Every healthy choice is a victory.</p>
                </div>

                <!-- Card 4: Rest & De-stress -->
                <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md hover:shadow-xl transition-shadow duration-300">
                    <img src="https://placehold.co/60x60/a8e063/ffffff?text=ðŸŒ™" alt="Moon Icon" class="card-icon mx-auto mb-4 rounded-full">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 text-center text-green-700">4. Rest & De-stress</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600">Poor sleep and high stress can raise blood sugar levels. Aim for 7-8 hours of quality sleep per night. Practice stress-reducing activities like meditation, deep breathing, yoga, or spending time in nature. Your mental health is key to your physical health.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
